## APL DESIGN RULES

### Layout Constraints (Echo Show 10)
- Screen: 1280×800 pixels
- Safe area margins: 24dp all sides
- Never use fixed pixel widths — always use percentages or dp
- Test RTL (right-to-left) for all Arabic text containers
- Arabic text must have `direction: RTL` and appropriate font

### Color Palette (strictly follow FDD.md)
```
Background:        #0D1B2A  (deep navy)
Prayer time text:  #D4AF37  (gold)
Next prayer:       #FFFFFF  (white, highlighted)
Past prayers:      #4A4A4A  (dimmed grey)
Countdown normal:  #FFFFFF
Countdown warning: #FFA500  (< 10 minutes)
Countdown urgent:  #FF4444  (< 1 minute)
Hadith text:       #E8E8E8
Header accent:     #4ECDC4  (teal)
```

### Fonts
- Use `Amazon Ember` for English text (built into Alexa)
- Use `Noto Naskh Arabic` for Arabic text
- Prayer time sizes: 42dp bold
- Countdown: 36dp bold
- Hadith text: 22dp regular

---

## CONTENT MANAGEMENT

### Hadith/Verse JSON Format
```javascript
// Always follow this schema — do not change field names
{
  "hadiths": [
    { "id": 1, "text": "Arabic text here", "source": "رواه البخاري" }
  ],
  "verses": [
    { "id": 1, "text": "﴿ Arabic verse ﴾", "surah": "البقرة: 201" }
  ]
}
```

### Content Rotation Logic
- Rotate sequentially (not randomly) to ensure all content is shown
- Store current index in Lambda context or EventBridge state
- Cycle: hadiths first, then verses, then repeat
- Never show same content twice in a row

