## WHAT NOT TO DO

- ❌ Never hardcode city/country — always use env vars
- ❌ Never use lat/lng directly — use city-based `timingsByCity` endpoint
- ❌ Never set `school=0` (Shafi) — this app uses Hanafi (`school=1`) by default
- ❌ Never store API keys in code — use AWS Secrets Manager or env vars
- ❌ Never make the S3 audio bucket public
- ❌ Never inline APL JSON inside Lambda handler code
- ❌ Never use `setTimeout` inside Lambda (use EventBridge instead)
- ❌ Never ignore AlAdhan API failures — always fallback gracefully
- ❌ Never change the prayer order: Fajr, Dhuhr, Asr, Maghrib, Isha
- ❌ Never use AWS SDK v2 — always use v3 (`@aws-sdk/client-*`)
- ❌ Never commit `.env` files or `samconfig.toml` with real values
- ❌ Never publish skill without testing Adhan audio on physical Echo Show

